|crew3_up         = [[Russell Schweickart|Russell L. Schweickart]]
|flights3_up      = Only
|notes            = Like [[Apollo 8]], the crew of Apollo 9 consisted of two [[Project Gemini|Gemini]]&lt;br/&gt;veterans and one rookie.
}}

===Backup crew===
{{Spaceflight crew
|terminology      = Astronaut
|position1        = Commander
|crew1_up         = [[Pete Conrad|Charles Conrad, Jr]]
|position2        = Command Module Pilot
|crew2_up         = [[Richard F. Gordon, Jr.]]
|position3        =  Lunar Module Pilot
|crew3_up         = [[Alan Bean|Alan L. Bean]]
|notes            = The backup crew became the prime crew on [[Apollo 12]].
}}

Originally [[Clifton Williams]] was the lunar module pilot for the backup crew. He died on October 5, 1967, in a [[T-38 Talon|T-38]] crash. His spot was given to Alan Bean. Later, when the backup crew flew [[Apollo 12]], a fourth star was added to their mission patch in remembrance of him.

===Support crew===
* [[Fred Haise|Fred W. Haise, Jr]]
* [[Jack R. Lousma]]
* [[Edgar Mitchell|Edgar D. Mitchell]]
* [[Al Worden|Alfred M. Worden]]

===Flight directors===
* [[Gene Kranz]], White team
* [[Gerry Griffin]], Gold team
* Pete Frank, Orange team

