==Spacecraft location==
The Apollo 9 Command Module ''Gumdrop'' (1969-018A) is on display at the [[San Diego Air &amp; Space Museum]], [[San Diego, California]]. Its service module was jettisoned shortly after the deorbit burn and decayed during reentry of the command module.

The ascent stage of LM-3 ''Spider'' (1969-018C) decayed on October 23, 1981.

The descent stage of LM-3 ''Spider'' (1969-018D) decayed March 22, 1969.

The upper stage of the Apollo 9 Saturn V, S-IVB-504N, (1969-018B) is in heliocentric (solar) orbit.

