==Events==
* [[475]] &amp;ndash; The [[Roman Empire|Roman]] [[general]] [[Orestes (Roman soldier)|Orestes]] forces western [[Roman Emperors|Roman Emperor]] [[Julius Nepos]] to flee his [[capital city]], [[Ravenna]].
* [[489]] &amp;ndash; [[Theodoric the Great|Theodoric]], king of the [[Ostrogoths]] defeats [[Odoacer]] at the [[Battle of Isonzo (489)|Battle of Isonzo]], forcing his way into [[Italy]].
*[[1189]] &amp;ndash; [[Third Crusade]]: the Crusaders begin the [[Siege of Acre (1189–1191)|Siege of Acre]] under [[Guy of Lusignan]]
*[[1349]] &amp;ndash; 6,000 Jews are killed in [[Mainz]], accused of being the cause of the plague.
*[[1511]] &amp;ndash; The [[History of Portugal|Portuguese]] conquer [[Malacca]].
*[[1521]] &amp;ndash; The [[Ottoman Turks]] occupy [[Belgrade]].
*[[1542]] &amp;ndash; [[Turkish-Portuguese War (1538-1557)]] &amp;ndash; [[Battle of Wofla]]: the Portuguese are scattered, their leader [[Christovão da Gama]] is captured and later executed.
*[[1609]] &amp;ndash; [[Henry Hudson]] discovers [[Delaware Bay]].
*[[1619]] &amp;ndash; [[Ferdinand II of Germany|Ferdinand II]] is elected [[emperor]] of the [[Holy Roman Empire]].
*[[1640]] &amp;ndash; [[Bishops' Wars#Second Bishops' War (1640)|Second Bishop's War]]: King [[Charles I of England|Charles I]]'s English army loses to a [[Covenanter|Scottish Covenanter]] force at the [[Battle of Newburn]].
*[[1789]] &amp;ndash; [[William Herschel]] discovers a new moon of Saturn.
*[[1810]] &amp;ndash; [[Battle of Grand Port]] – the French accept the surrender of a [[British Navy]] fleet.
*[[1830]] &amp;ndash; The [[Baltimore and Ohio Railroad]]'s  new ''[[Tom Thumb (locomotive)|Tom Thumb]]'' steam locomotive races a horse-drawn  car, presaging steam's role in US railroading.
*[[1845]] &amp;ndash; The first issue of ''[[Scientific American]]'' magazine is published.
*[[1849]] &amp;ndash; After a month-long siege, [[Venice]], which had declared itself independent, surrenders to [[Austria]].
*[[1859]] &amp;ndash; A geomagnetic storm causes the [[Aurora Borealis]] to shine so brightly that it is seen clearly over parts of USA, Europe, and even as far away as Japan.
*[[1862]] &amp;ndash; [[American Civil War]]: [[Second Battle of Bull Run]], also known as the Battle of Second Manassas.
*[[1867]] &amp;ndash; The [[United States]] takes possession of the, at this point unoccupied, [[Midway Atoll]].
*[[1879]] &amp;ndash; [[Cetshwayo]], last king of the [[Zulu people|Zulu]]s, is captured by the [[United Kingdom of Great Britain and Ireland|British]].
*[[1898]] &amp;ndash; [[Caleb Bradham]] renames his carbonated soft drink &quot;[[Pepsi-Cola]]&quot;.
*[[1901]] &amp;ndash; [[Silliman University]] is founded in the [[Philippines]]. The first [[United States|American]] [[private school|private]] school in the country.
*[[1913]] &amp;ndash; [[Wilhelmina of the Netherlands|Queen Wilhelmina]] opens the [[Peace Palace]] in [[The Hague]].
*[[1914]] &amp;ndash; [[World War I]]: the [[Royal Navy]] defeats the [[Germany|German]] fleet in the [[Battle of Heligoland Bight]].
*  1914   &amp;ndash;   World War I: German troops conquer [[Namur (city)|Namur]].
*[[1916]] &amp;ndash;   World War I: Germany declares war on [[Romania]].
*  1916   &amp;ndash;   World War I: [[Italy]] declares war on Germany.
*[[1917]] &amp;ndash; Ten [[Suffragettes]] are arrested while picketing the [[White House]].
*[[1924]] &amp;ndash; The [[Georgia (country)|Georgian]] opposition stages the [[August Uprising]] against the [[Soviet Union]].
*[[1931]] &amp;ndash; [[France]] and [[Soviet Union]] sign a treaty of non-aggression.
*[[1937]] &amp;ndash; [[Toyota Motors]] becomes an independent company.
*[[1943]] &amp;ndash; [[World War II]]: in [[Denmark]], a [[general strike]] against the [[Nazism|Nazi]] occupation is started.
*[[1944]] &amp;ndash;   World War II: [[Marseille]] and [[Toulon]] are liberated.
*[[1953]] &amp;ndash; [[Nippon Television]] broadcasts [[Japan]]'s first television show, including its first TV advertisement.
*[[1955]] &amp;ndash; [[African American|Black]] teenager [[Emmett Till]] is murdered in [[Mississippi]], galvanizing the nascent [[American Civil Rights Movement]].
*[[1957]] &amp;ndash; [[United States Senate|U.S. Senator]] [[Strom Thurmond]] begins a [[filibuster]] to prevent the Senate from voting on [[Civil Rights Act of 1957]]; he stopped speaking 24 hours and 18 minutes later, the longest filibuster ever conducted by a single Senator.
*[[1961]] &amp;ndash; [[Motown]] releases what would be its first #1 hit, &quot;[[Please Mr. Postman]]&quot; by [[The Marvelettes]].
*[[1963]] &amp;ndash; [[March on Washington for Jobs and Freedom]]: [[Martin Luther King, Jr.]] gives his ''[[I have a dream|I Have a Dream]]'' speech
*  1963   &amp;ndash; [[Career Girls Murders|Emily Hoffert and Janice Wylie]] are murdered in their [[Upper East Side|Manhattan]] flat, prompting the events that would lead to the passing of the [[Miranda warning|Miranda Rights]].
*  [[1964]]   &amp;ndash; The [[1964 Philadelphia race riot|Philadelphia race riot]] begins.
*[[1968]] &amp;ndash; [[Riot]]s in [[Chicago|Chicago, Illinois]], during the [[1968 Democratic National Convention|Democratic National Convention]].
*[[1979]] &amp;ndash; An [[provisional IRA|IRA]] bomb explodes on the [[Grand Place]] in [[Brussels]].
*[[1981]] &amp;ndash; The [[National Centers for Disease Control]] announce a high incidence of [[pneumocystis]] and [[Kaposi's sarcoma]] in gay men. These will soon be recognized as symptoms of an [[immune system|immune]] disorder, which will be called [[AIDS]].
*[[1986]] &amp;ndash; [[United States Navy]] [[Officer (armed forces)|officer]] Jerry A. Whitworth is sentenced to 365 years [[imprisonment]] for [[espionage]] for the [[Soviet Union]].
*[[1988]] &amp;ndash; [[Ramstein airshow disaster]]: three aircraft of the [[Frecce Tricolori]] demonstration team collide and the wreckage falls into the crowd. 75 are killed and 346 seriously injured.
*[[1990]] &amp;ndash; [[Iraq]] declares [[Kuwait]] to be its newest [[Provinces of Iraq|province]].
*  1990   &amp;ndash; The [[Plainfield Tornado]]: an F5 tornado hits in [[Plainfield, Illinois]], and [[Joliet, Illinois]], killing 28 people.
*[[1991]] &amp;ndash; [[Ukraine]] declares its independence from the Soviet Union.
*  1991   &amp;ndash; Collapse of the Soviet Union &amp;ndash; [[Mikhail Gorbachev]] resigns as Secretary of the Soviet Communist Party.
*[[1996]] &amp;ndash; [[Charles, Prince of Wales]] and [[Diana, Princess of Wales]] divorce.
*[[1998]] &amp;ndash; [[Pakistan]]'s [[National Assembly of Pakistan|National Assembly]] passes a [[Constitution of Pakistan|constitutional]] amendment to make the &quot;[[Qur'an]] and [[Sunnah]]&quot; the &quot;supreme law&quot; but the bill is defeated in the [[Senate of Pakistan|Senate]].
*[[2003]] &amp;ndash; An [[2003 London blackout|electricity blackout]] cuts off power to around 500,000 people living in south east England and brings 60% of London's underground rail network to a halt.
*[[2005]] &amp;ndash; [[Hurricane Katrina]] begins to make landfall in [[Louisiana]] and [[Mississippi]] in the afternoon, and brings the most severe damage to [[Slidell, Louisiana|Slidell]] and [[New Orleans, Louisiana|New Orleans]].

